So far as we know, the rest of the earthly creation is not. Nature therefore attracts us because of what we see as its innocence. In what grammarians call the \"pathetic fallacy\", we project our own feelings on to nature – the \"joy\" of the song of the lark ascending, the \"sadness\" of the cypress.
